HEADWORD: Extravascular
<hw>Ex`tra*vas"cu*lar</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<fld>(Anat.)</fld> <sd>(a)</sd> <def>Outside the vessels; -- said of the
substance of all the tissues.</def> <sd>(b)</sd> <def>Destitute of
vessels; non-vascular.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Extravenate</ent>⟦br⟧
